From 5b82853ee67f3f2166a3a090ff286995a959503f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: michael <michael@dotfiles.local>
Date: Sun, 8 Mar 2026 17:08:17 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] feat: add focus ring fade animation and gradient rotation

Add two new optional animation features for the focus ring:

- Fade: smoothly fades the focus ring in/out on focus changes
  using an EaseOutCubic curve. Configurable via `fade-duration-ms`
  (default: off, recommended: 500-1000ms).

- Gradient rotation: continuously rotates the gradient angle while
  a window is focused. Configurable via `gradient-spin-speed` in
  degrees per second (default: off, e.g. 90 for a slow spin).

Both features are opt-in and have no effect unless explicitly
configured in the `focus-ring {}` config block.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>

fix: render focus ring during fade-out animation

Previously the ring was only rendered when focused, causing it to
disappear instantly instead of fading out.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

feat: add border color fade animation and gradient rotation

Bring fade-duration-ms and gradient-spin-speed support to the border
decoration, matching the existing focus ring capabilities. Uses a
two-layer crossfade approach for smooth color interpolation between
active and inactive border colors during focus changes.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

fix: apply gradient rotation to non-border focus ring path

The gradient_angle_offset was only applied in the border code path,
causing gradient spin to work on windows with rounded corners but
not on windows rendered without the border shader.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

